ge: Cookbooks and American Culture''. University of Pennsylvania Press. pp. 67-68. {{ISBN|978-0812249170}}</ref> He recommended eating all kinds of meat (except pig), [[game (hunting)|game]], sea-food, eggs, fruit and green [[vegetable]]s.<ref>Thompson, Vance. (1914). [https://archive.org/details/eatgrowthinmahda00thomiala/page/42 ''Eat and Grow Thin'']. New York: E. P. Dutton. pp. 42-43</ref> The book was criticized for misrepresenting nutritional science.<ref name=\"Elias\"/>\n\nPhysiologist [[Graham Lusk]] commented that the advice from the book \"made so many of my friends so utterly miserable that I am sure that in the end it will counteract its own message.\"<ref>Lusk, Graham. (1917). [https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=hvd.tz17se&view=1up&seq=355 ''Food In War Time'']. ''The Scientific Monthly'' 5: 307.</ref>\n\n==Publications==\n[[File:Eat and Grow Thin.png|thumb|''Eat and Grow Thin'', 1914]]\n\n*[https://archive.org/details/frenchportraits00thomiala ''French Portraits: Being Appreciations of the Writers of Young France''] (1900) \n*''Spinners of Life'' (1904)\n*''Diplomatic Mysteries'' (1905)\n*[https://archive.org/details/lifeofethelbertn000845mbp ''The Life of Ethelbert Nevin''] (1913) \n*[https://archive.org/details/egobookbookofsel00thomiala ''The Ego Book: A Book of Selfish Ideals''] (1914) \n*''The Night Watchman and Other Poems'' (1914)\n*[https://archive.org/details/eatgrowthinmahda00thomiala ''Eat and Grow Thin: The Mahdah Menus''] (1914) \n*[https://archive.org/details/drinkbesober00thom/page/n6 ''Drink and Be Sober''] (1915)\n*[https://archive.org/details/versenight00thomrich ''Verse''] (1915) \n*[https://archive.org/details/carnivalofdestin00thomiala ''The Carnival of Destiny''] (1916) \n*''The Peace Girl'' (1916)\n*[https://archive.org/details/womanandword00thomuoft ''Woman''] (1917) \n*[https://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/100630573 ''Live and Be Young''] (1920)\n*''The Pointed Tower'' (1923)\n*''The Green Ray'' (1924)\n*''The Scarlet Iri